## 🔐 Configuration

### NuGet Deployment Config
**Location:** `%OneDriveCommercial%\AzureAccessTokens.json`

**Format:**
```json
[
  {
    "Id": "Dedge_NugetAccessToken",
    "Token": "YOUR_PAT",
    "Email": "your.email@company.com",
    "ProjectName": "Dedge",
    "ExpirationDate": "2026-12-17",
    "LastUpdated": "2025-12-18",
    "Notes": "PAT requires 'Packaging (Read, write, & manage)' permissions."
  }
]
```

### Database Configuration
**Location:** `C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\DedgeCommon\Configfiles\DatabasesV2.json`

Contains configurations for all databases (FKMTST, FKMPRD, INLTST, etc.) with:
- Database names and aliases
- Server connections
- Access points (Alias, PrimaryDb)
- Authentication types (Kerberos, Password)

