## 📱 Long-Running Operations Notification

**ONLY send SMS when operation takes more than 5 minutes from when agent started working.**

**How to track time:**
- Note when agent started working on the task
- Before sending SMS, calculate elapsed time
- Only send if elapsed time > 5 minutes
- Track time from first tool call, not from user message

**Auto-detect SMS number:**
```powershell
# Calculate elapsed time first
$elapsedMinutes = ([DateTime]::Now - $startTime).TotalMinutes

if ($elapsedMinutes -gt 5) {
    $smsNumber = switch ($env:USERNAME) {
        "FKGEISTA" { "+4797188358" }
        "FKSVEERI" { "+4795762742" }
        "FKMISTA"  { "+4799348397" }
        "FKCELERI" { "+4745269945" }
        default    { "+4797188358" } # Fallback to FKGEISTA
    }
    Send-Sms $smsNumber "<summary of what changed and short result>"
}
```

**SMS message format:**
- Keep under 160 characters
- Include: operation type, files affected, and status (success/failure)
- Example: `Send-Sms "+4797188358" "DedgeCommon v1.5.20 deployed. WorkObject pattern added. All tests passed."`

**When to send:**
- ONLY after operation completes AND elapsed time > 5 minutes
- Before final response to user
- Include error summary if operation failed
- **Send to the current logged-in user** based on `$env:USERNAME`

**Do NOT send SMS for:**
- Operations under 5 minutes (MOST IMPORTANT - check elapsed time!)
- Interactive operations requiring user input during execution
- Simple read-only queries
- Quick fixes, simple builds, or fast deployments

**Example logic:**
```powershell
# At start of task
$taskStartTime = [DateTime]::Now

# At end of task  
$elapsedTime = ([DateTime]::Now - $taskStartTime).TotalMinutes

if ($elapsedTime -gt 5) {
    # Send SMS notification
    Send-Sms $smsNumber "Task completed after $([Math]::Round($elapsedTime, 1)) minutes: <summary>"
}
else {
    # Skip SMS for quick operations
    Write-Host "Operation completed in $([Math]::Round($elapsedTime, 1)) minutes (no SMS sent)"
}
```

